Burkina’s Faso’s Presidential Guard Mutinies in Capital Over Pay Dispute

-- B y   S i m o n   G o n g o
-- 
2011-04-15T09:37:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/burkina-s-faso-s-presidential-guard-mutinies-in-capital-over-pay-dispute.html
The presidential guard of Burkina
Faso’s President Blaise Compaore, has mutinied, residents of the
country’s capital, Ougadougou, and an an army spokesman said.  Shots were heard from a military camp overnight, Chantal
Nikiema, a resident of the capital, said in an interview today.
The mutiny was confirmed by Moussa Cisse, a spokesman for the
army who said the revolt is related to a pay dispute.  Agence France Presse reported that Compaore has fled the
capital to his home town of Ziniare, citing an unidentified
military official.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Gongo in Ouagadougou at 
 sgongo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
